The setup page is automatically opened when extension installation has completed. The Granite.Code
icon also appears in the Activity Bar. Clicking this opens the Granite.Code chat sidebar.
While the extension is yet to be set up, the chat sidebar
shows a placeholder Welcome View. This contains a button
which opens the setup assistant view.
All the text in these mockups is extremely tentative and will need to be revised as the
Granite.Code identity and feature set are developed.
If Ollama is installed when setup starts, we open on this step.
Large or small is automatically selected based on the machine's capabilities.
The UI for this page is modelled on a walkthrough: each list row can be expanded and, when a row has
been completed, it collapses and the next in the sequence expands.
When the model has been downloaded, Granite.Code should be ready to be used. At this point:
- The status bar item is shown
- The quick start tutorial is opened
The final step of the setup assistant is a prompt to start using the AI. This is marked as complete once
the user clicks the button or enters a query in the sidebar.
